                UNITED STATES COURTS FOR THE DISTRICT OF UTAH
            2002 WINTER OLYMPICS NOTICE TO THE BAR AND THE PUBLIC

   Bankruptcy Court Memorandum regarding Teleconferencing during the 2002
                            Winter Olympics (PDF)

                          BUSINESS HOURS DURING THE
   2002 OLYMPICS

   During the 2002 Olympic Winter Games in Salt Lake City, the business
   hours of the United States District and Bankruptcy Courts for the
   District of Utah will be adjusted as follows.

   Beginning on Thursday, February 7, 2002, and continuing through Monday,
   February 25, 2002, daily weekday business hours for the District Clerks
   Office and Bankruptcy Clerks Office will be 9:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m.
   Access to the Frank E. Moss U.S. Courthouse will be limited to these
   business hours.

   The courthouse will be closed on Monday, February 18, 2002, in honor of
   Presidents Day, a federal holiday.

   The District Courts 24-hour filing box will remain in operation
   throughout the Winter Olympics with no change in current requirements
   or procedures. Papers relating to bankruptcy proceedings should be
   mailed or delivered to the Bankruptcy Court during the hours noted.

   We appreciate your cooperation with this schedule change and anticipate
   a smooth return to the regular course of business following the 2002
   Olympic Games.

   For information, call the District Court Clerks Office at (801)
   524-6100 or the Bankruptcy Court Clerks Office at (801) 524-6687.

